imbor-term:bf417ed1-cb8c-4acd-98d4-95a4119a4730 a skos:Concept;
  skos:definition "The bar is a non-SI unit of pressure, defined by the IUPAC as exactly equal to 100,000\\a. It is about equal to the atmospheric pressure on Earth at sea level, and since 1982 the IUPAC has recommended that the standard for atmospheric pressure should be harmonized to \\\\(100,000\\\\,Pa = 1 \\\\,bar \\\\approx 750.0616827\\\\, Torr\\\\). "@nl;
